description.narrative: This activity (Running costs) is a component of Humanitarian Assistance in Response to Pakistan Floods 2010 reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Humanitarian assistance' and a budget of £1,008,441. This component benefits Pakistan, and works in the following sector(s): Relief co-ordination and support services. , with the following implementing partners: British Deputy High Commission (BDHC), British High Commission, Pak, Coffey International Development, Crown Agents Limited, CROWN RELOCATIONS UK, Foreign, Commonwealth and Development Office. The start date is 19-08-2010 and the end date is 15-12-2012.
